== Rice and Coconut ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions; preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and mince half the @shallot{1} (whole 
shallot for 4 servings). Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Mince or 
grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Zest and quarter @lime{1} (quarter both limes for 4). 
Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(leaves and stems). Finely chop 
@chili pepper{1}.

Place @shredded coconut{1/4%cup} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Cook, 
stirring, until golden brown and toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer 
to a #small bowl{}. In a #small pot{}, combine @basmati rice{1/2%cup} and 
3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings). Bring to a boil, then cover and 
reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered 
off heat until ready to serve.

== Mini Bell Peppers ==

While rice cooks, toss @mini bell peppers{6%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a 
large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon}; season generously with @salt{} and 
@pepper{}. Roast on top rack until softened and lightly charred, 
~{20-25%minutes}.

== Pork and Chutney ==

Meanwhile, pat @pork tenderloin{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all 
over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in #pan{} used for coconut over 
medium heat. Add pork and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, 
~{4-8%minutes}. Transfer pork to a second baking sheet. Roast on middle rack 
until cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}. Let pork rest a few minutes after 
removing from oven, then thinly slice crosswise.

Heat @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) and a drizzle of oil in pan used for 
pork over medium-high heat. Add garlic, ginger, shallot, half the 
@curry powder{1%tablespoon} (use the rest as you like), and chili to taste. 
Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in juice from half the lime 
and @sugar{2%teaspoon} (4 tsp for 4) until sugar is dissolved, ~{30%seconds}. 
Add @pineapple{8%ounce} and its juice. Bring to a boil; reduce to a low simmer. 
Cook until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn off heat. Stir in half the cilantro; 
season with salt and pepper.

> If chutney is too thick, stir in a splash of water.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 
servings), lime zest, and toasted coconut; divide between plates. Stir any resting 
juices from pork into chutney. Arrange pork and mini bell peppers over rice. Top 
pork with chutney and remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the 
side.